Sentencas: A new heterostructured (La,Sr)(2)FeO4_delta (LSF214)-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3_delta (LSF113) electrode has been synthesized to improve the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This new materials system was fabricated by the deposition of Sr(NO3)(2) into the LSF113 framework followed by subsequent heat treatment, resulting in a new three-dimensional (3D) LSF214-LSF113 heterostructured electrode.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This material system consists of a with Ruddlesden-Popper (R-P) LSF214 phase formed on the surface of the LSF113 framework.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The ORR activity has been enhanced by 1 order of magnitude using the LSF214-LSF113 heterostructured electrode.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The ORR enhancement was the result of higher catalytic activity of the LSF214 phase and a mismatch in the lattice parameter between LSF214 and LSF113 regions which results in oxygen molecule adsorption and oxygen vacancy formation become more favered.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy measurements revealed that the presence of LSF214 reduced the polarization resistance of the LSF113 electrode on a ceria-based electrolyte.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The high frequency resistance (RH) and low frequency resistance (RL) decreased substantially due to the enhanced oxygen transport process and accelerated oxygen incorporation rate in the LSF214-LSF113 heterostructured electrode.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The heterostructured LSF224-LSF113 electrode provides a promising new approach to improve the oxygen reduction reaction activity through multiphase materials systems with tailored microstructures.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Activity on Ruddlesden-Popper Phase Decorated La0.8Sr0.2FeO3-δ 3D Heterostructured Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
